		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Nusa Penida",
					"url": "https://goo.gl/maps/3oFDwsurGGbmha3Z9",
					"bold": true
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "a"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Lebongan",
					"url": "https://goo.gl/maps/4eEwwS84EdHGdfBw6",
					"bold": true
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "is an unassuming yet relatively large archipelago between Bali and Lombok that shouldn’t be missed. The island belongs to"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Bali",
					"url": "https://lowcost-traveling.com/en/asia-en/bali/"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "and offers beautiful coastal spots with photogenic cliffs. Beautiful views, swimming with mantas, beaches, dolphins, snorkeling on coral reefs, scuba diving, and plenty of warmth—all within the small area of the three islands: Nusa Penida, Ceningan, and Lebongan."
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "\n"
				}
			]
		},
