		{
			"type": "paragraph",
			"children": [
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "These three stunning Gili islands, located in Indonesia between"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Bali",
					"url": "https://lowcost-traveling.com/en/asia-en/bali/"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "and"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Lombok",
					"url": "https://lowcost-traveling.com/en/asia-en/lombok/"
				},
				{
					"type": "text",
					"text": ", are the perfect place for relaxation, fun, diving, snorkeling, and more. Surrounded by coral reefs, the islands welcome daily visits from turtles, allowing for close encounters. No motor vehicles are allowed on the islands except for electric scooters, so transportation mainly involves horse-drawn carts or bicycles. The islands are relatively small (around 2 km in diameter), easily walkable in their entirety."
				}
			]
		},
